release_note: Devices compatibility improvement Crash bug fix Performance enhancement
Fixed empty phrases when select Japanese as the source language minor bugs fix performance improvement
Fixed small bug when upgraded on iPad Revised error messages

The biggest update ever! Thank you for all your feedback to help us improve Tap Say. We will continue to add more improvements in the future. Fixed Spanish content download problem Added 5 new languages includes Spanish Latin Arabic Brazilian Portuguese Russian Updated the UI Added the ability to reorder your favourite second language Support search in phonetic and native translation. Support the ability to switch between male or female voiceover in Thai language Support the ability to slow down audio speed Added new settings with auto play on off and show hide transliteration Minor bugs fixed Improved performance Thank you for using Tap Say. We appreciate your time to give us rating and review if you like our app.
Added Cantonese as our 12th languages in the app! More languages to come.
This Tap Say app is now compatible with iOS8 and support iPhone 6 and 6 iPhone 6 plus. Coming soon: Additional languages

IMPORTANT: Please be advised that shortly after release we discovered there is a bug affecting some users on iPad. The bug has been fixed but we are waiting for Apple to approve the update. As soon as the update is approved we will release to all users. Sorry for any inconvenience caused. DO NOT UPDATE IF YOU ARE ON AN IPAD iOS6 iPhone5 compatibility
